Software Sustainability Evaluation Pipeline - Installation

1) Clone the repository
   git clone <your_repo_url>
   cd <repo>

2) Create a virtual environment (recommended)
   python -m venv .venv
   # Windows PowerShell:
   .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
   # macOS/Linux:
   source .venv/bin/activate

3) Install Python dependencies
   pip install -r requirements.txt

4) Configure environment variables
   - Edit one of:
     configs/env.ps1
     configs/env.sh
   - Required values:
     SONAR_HOST_URL, SONAR_TOKEN
     LLM_PROVIDER, LLM_MODEL, LLM_BASE_URL
     LLM_API_KEY (for hosted APIs)

5) Basic smoke test
   python -c "from pipeline.configs import config; print(config.BASE_DIR)"

6) Run core pipeline (canonical)
   python -m pipeline.main

Expected outputs after full run
   data/results/git/git_metrics.csv
   data/results/sonar/sonar_metrics.csv
   data/results/llm/llm_metrics_<model>_runNNN.csv
   data/results/merged/final_dataset.csv

Holistic evaluator output
   data/results/holistic/holistic_assessments_<model>_runNNN.csv

Optional research workflows
   python -m experiments.holistic_evaluator
   python -m experiments.refactoring_study
   python -m analysis.rq_process_sustainability
